\" | 28.5<br />(83.3)\n| style=\"background:#F10000;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 31.2<br />(88.2)\n| style=\"background:#E80000;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 32.2<br />(89.0)\n| style=\"background:#E10000;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 32.8<br />(91.0)\n| style=\"background:#E40000;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 31.9<br />(89.4)\n| style=\"background:#F30000;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 29.7<br />(85.5)\n| style=\"background:#FF1B00;color:#FFFFFF;\" | 27.1<br />(80.8)\n| style=\"background:#FF5A00;color:#000000;\" | 23.3<br />(74.0)\n| style=\"background:#FF2200;color:#FFFFFF;border-left-width:medium\"|27.1<br />(80.8)\n\n|-\n! Average [[Ultraviolet index]]\n| style=\"background:#f85900;color:#000000;\" | 6\n| style=\"background:#d8001d;color:#000000;\" | 8\n| style=\"background:#d8001d;color:#000000;\" | 10\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11+\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11+\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11+\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11+\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11+\n| style=\"background:#6b49c8;color:#000000;\" | 11\n| style=\"background:#d8001d;color:#000000;\" | 8\n| style=\"background:#f85900;color:#000000;\" | 6\n| style=\"background:#f7e400;color:#000000;\" | 5\n| style=\"background:#d8001d;color:#000000;border-left-width:medium\"|9.1\n\n|-\n! colspan=\"14\" style=\"background:#F8F9FA;font-weight:normal;font-size:95%;\" | Source #1: seatemperature.org<ref name=\"Seatemperature\">{{cite web |url=http://www.seatemperature.org/middle-east/united-arab-emirates/dubai-december.htm |title=Monthly Dubai water temperature chart |publisher=Seatemperatures.org |accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"14\" style=\"background:#F8F9FA;font-weight:normal;font-size:95%;\" | Source #2: Weather Atlas<ref name=\"Weather Atlas\">{{cite web |url=https://www.weather-atlas.com/en/united-arab-emirates/dubai-climate |title=Dubai, United Arab Emirates \u2013 Climate data |publisher=Weather Atlas |access-date=8 March 2017}}</ref>\n|}<section end=\"weatherbox\" />\n\n== Seasonal climate ==\nThe climate of Dubai is warm and sunny due to its position near the line of the Tropic of Cancer.<ref name=\"dubai.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.dubai.com/v/geography/ |title=Dubai Geography \u2013 Information, climate and weather in Dubai |publisher=Dubai.com |date=2013-05-27 |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref> During the winter season it has an average daytime temperature of {{convert|25|C|F}}. Nighttime temperatures near the coastline range between {{convert|12|C|F}} to {{convert|15|C|F}}, while in the desert they are {{convert|5|C|F}} with the nights being relatively cool throughout the year. Near coastal areas humidity averages between 50% and 60%. In the summer, the weather in Dubai is very hot and humid, with temperatures reaching {{convert|45|C|F}} for many days. Even the sea temperature reaches {{convert|37|C|F}}, with humidity averaging over 90%.<ref name=\"dubai.com\" />\nRainfall in Dubai is infrequent and does not last for a long period. It mostly rains during the winter period between December and March in the form of short downpours and an occasional thunderstorm. On average, rain falls only five days a year.<ref name=\"dubai.com\" />{{Contradict-inline|reason=Meteorological Office data contradicts official city website on rainfall days.|date=May 2019}}\n\nFebruary is the wettest month in Dubai with an average of {{convert|35|mm|in|abbr=on}} of rain.<ref name=\"visit-dubai-city.com\" /> The weather in Dubai is extremely dry in the month of June with little or no rain.<ref name=\"visit-dubai-city.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.visit-dubai-city.com/weather-in-dubai.html |title=Weather in Dubai City \u2013 Information on the Weather in Dubai, UAE |publisher=Visit-dubai-city.com |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref> March and December also record some amount of rainfall. The rainfall during January, April, July, October and November are about average while the amount of rain in May, August and September are comparatively lower.<ref name=\"visit-dubai-city.com\" />\nThe hottest month is August\nAverage temperature-36 degrees \nColdest month is January\nAverage temperature-19 degrees\nDubai is extremely hot in June July and August\nVery hot in may September and early october\nWarm in late October early November and mid April to early may\nPlease tell mild and cool in mid November December January February and March and early April\n\n== Climatic conditions by month ==\nIn January the average maximum daytime temperature in Dubai is {{convert|24|C|F}}. The average rainfall is 10&nbsp;mm (0.4&nbsp;inches) of, with rain generally falling on just two days of the month. While the average sea temperature in January is {{convert|22|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\">{{cite web |author=Weather2Flights.com |url=http://www.weather2flights.com/airports/index.php?airport=DXB#weather_october |title=Airports \u2013 Who flies there? |publisher=Weather2flights.com |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref> On January 15, 2008 {{convert|110|mm|in|abbr=on}} of rain was recorded in 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/uae/environment/downpour-continues-as-dubai-receives-record-rainfall-1.78027 |title=Downpour continues as Dubai receives record rainfall |work=Gulf News |date=2008-01-16 |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref>\n\nIn February the average maximum daytime temperature in Dubai is {{convert|25|C|F}}. The average rainfall is {{convert|35|mm|in|abbr=on}} during February. While the average sea temperature is {{convert|22|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn March the average temperature is {{convert|28|C|F}}, with moderate heat and humidity. The average rainfall is {{convert|27|mm|in|abbr=on}} during March, with rain generally falling on just four days of the month. While the average sea temperature is {{convert|23|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn April the average daytime temperature is {{convert|32|C|F}}, with high heat and humidity. The average rainfall is {{convert|8|mm|in|abbr=on}} with rain generally falling on just two days of the month. The average sea temperature in April is {{convert|24|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn May the average temperature is {{convert|37|C|F}}, with extreme heat and humidity. The average rainfall is {{convert|1|mm|in|abbr=on}} during May, with rain generally falling on just one day of the month. The average sea temperature is {{convert|28|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn June the average temperature is {{convert|39|C|F}}, with extreme heat and humidity. The average rainfall is less than {{convert|1|mm|in|abbr=on}} during June, with a possible chance of rainfall that could be expected to fall on one of the days of the month.<ref>https://www.khaleejtimes.com/news/weather/video-rain-hits-parts-of-dubai-sharjah-weather-warning-issued</ref> The average sea temperature in June is {{convert|31|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn July the average temperature is extremely high {{convert|42|C|F}} with extreme heat and humidity. The average rainfall is less than {{convert|1|mm|in|abbr=on}} during July, with a possible chance of rainfall that could be expected to fall on one of the days of the month. The average sea temperature in the month of July is {{convert|32|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn August the average temperature is {{convert|43|C|F}}, with extreme heat and humidity. The average rainfall is less than {{convert|1|mm|in|abbr=on}} during August, with a possible chance of rainfall that could be expected to fall on one of the days of the month.<ref>https://gulfnews.com/uae/weather/heres-why-uae-was-hit-by-rain-and-dust-storm-in-summer-1.65969554</ref> The average sea temperature in August is {{convert|32|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn September the average temperature is {{convert|39|C|F}}, with extreme heat and humidity. There is very little chance of any rainfall during September. Average sea temperature in September is {{convert|32|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn October the average temperature is {{convert|36|C|F}}, with very high heat and humidity. The average sea temperature around Dubai Airport in October is {{convert|30|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn November the average temperature is {{convert|31|C|F}}, with high heat and humidity. On average only {{convert|3|mm|in|abbr=on}} of rainfall may occur in November. Average sea temperature in November is {{convert|28|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\nIn December the average temperature is {{convert|26|C|F}}, cool to warm with high humidity. The average rainfall during the month is {{convert|15|mm|in|abbr=on}}. With rain generally falling on just 2 days of the month. The average sea temperature in December is {{convert|25|C|F}}.<ref name=\"weather2flights.com\" />\n\n== Sandstorms and Extreme Events ==\nDuring the summer season, a low pressure area develops over Dubai forcing strong north-westerly winds to blow from Saudi Arabia. These winds, also known as [[Shamal (wind)|Shamal]] (north) in Arabic, become gusty and unpredictable on reaching Dubai. Shamal boost up the desert sand and reduce visibility and the [[dust storm sandstorm]]s may last for several days. Notable sandstorms that hit Dubai during the last few years include:\n\n* On April 18, 2008 a severe sandstorm hit Dubai and reduced visibility to 1,500 meters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/uae/environment/severe-sandstorm-reduces-visibility-in-dubai-1.98596 |title=Severe sandstorm reduces visibility in Dubai |work=Gulf News |date=2008-04-19 |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref>\n* On March 10, 2009 a moderate sandstorm reached Dubai which lowered down the visibility and temperature.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/uae/environment/moderate-sandstorm-reaches-dubai-1.57127 |title=Moderate sandstorm reaches Dubai |work=Gulf News |date=2009-03-11 |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref>\n* On March 2, 2010 Strong winds caused sandstorms in Dubai and other regions of [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Earth Snapshot \u2013 Sandstorms Over Dubai, United Arab Emirates \u2013 March 2nd, 2010 |url=http://www.eosnap.com/image-of-the-day/sandstorms-over-dubai-united-arab-emirates-march-2nd-2010/ |website=eosnap.com |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=2 March 2010}}</ref>\n* On January 28, 2011 a sandstorm hit Dubai for a short time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kazmi |first1=Aftab |title=Sudden storm brings life to a halt in UAE |url=https://gulfnews.com/news/uae/weather/sudden-storm-brings-life-to-a-halt-in-uae-1.753793 |website=[[Gulf News]] | accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=29 January 2011}}</ref>\n* On February 26, 2012 a strong sandstorm hit Dubai and other parts of the country.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sandstorm rages across the UAE |url=https://gulfnews.com/news/uae/weather/sandstorm-rages-across-the-uae-1.986289 |website=Gulf News |accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=26 February 2012}}</ref>\n* On April 2, 2015 a very strong sandstorm hit Dubai and other parts of the country. It started to clear out closer to the evening. In some areas visibility use reduced to 500 metres.<ref>{{cite web |title=Major sandstorm blots out Dubai sky |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-32163590 |publisher=[[BBC News]] | accessdate=24 June 2018 |date=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n*On March 1, 2019, a strong sandstorm hit Dubai along with very strong winds after heavy rainfall, bringing temperatures down by  {{convert|10|C|F|abbr=}}.<ref>{{cite web |title=UAE weather: Rain and 60kph high winds lash the Emirates |url=https://www.thenational.ae/uae/environment/uae-weather-rain-and-60kph-high-winds-lash-the-emirates-1.831815 |website=The National |accessdate=16 November 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n*From January 7 to around January 12th ,2020, record breaking rains hit Dubai and other regions of the UAE . The incessant storms brought strong winds and hailstorms and brought down temperatures severely. Unusually heavy rain hit Dubai, with rainfall reaching 150 mm/hour for 2.5 hours, according to preliminary reports, the storms also flooded various regions of the emirate as well as flooded the Dubai Airport, leading to the cancellation of most flights. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khaleejtimes.com/news/weather/revealed-just-how-much-rain-did-dubai-receive|title=Revealed: Just how much rain did Dubai receive?|last=Reporter|first=Staff|website=Khaleej Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.ncms.ae/en#!/Radar_UAE_Dubai/26 Dubai weather] \u2013 UAE's National Center of Meteorology and Seismology\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100722193221/http://dubaihotels.ae/Weather/ Weather of Dubai]\n* [http://www.dreamsofdubai.com/dubai-climate-weather/ Dreamsofdubai]\n* [http://www.climate-charts.com/Locations/u/UE41194.php Climate-Charts.com]\n* [http://www.emirates247.com/news/emirates/dubai-gears-up-for-the-future-through-climate-change-adaptation-plan-2017-01-24-1.646945 Dubai Climate Change Adaptation Plan] \u2013 Emirates 24/7\n\n{{Dubai topics}}\n\n[[Category:Geography of Dubai]]\n[[Category:Climate of the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Climate by city|Dubai]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Dubai Skyline on 10 January 2008.jpg|270px|thumb|Clouds over Dubai in winter]]\nDubai has a [[hot desert climate]]. Dubai has two distinct seasons - summer and winter. Summer in Dubai begins around the last week of April and ends around the first week of October. This period is characterized by hot weather, warm winds and high humidity. Due to the city's close proximity to the sea the temperatures in Dubai are milder in summer in comparison to other Gulf cities such as Kuwait City and Riyadh. However this means the city has a high humidity which can make the weather very unpleasant. Rainfall is scarce during the summer months, but the windy conditions ensure there are frequent [[dust storms]]. Temperatures regularly climb above {{convert|38|C|0|abbr=on}} during this period and fall to around {{convert|26|C|0|abbr=on}} overnight. Winter in Dubai begins around the last week of October and lasts until the beginning of April. The winter season has the most pleasant weather, making it ideal for outdoor activities. Most of the precipitation takes place during this season. Strong thunderstorms are not uncommon to the city during this period, this is accompanied by strong north-westerly winds and lower temperatures. Average daytime high during the winter season is around {{convert|22|C|0|abbr=on}} with overnight lows of {{convert|12|C|0|abbr=on}}. Rainfall has been increasing over the past few decades accumulating to {{convert|130|mm|2|abbr=on}} per year.<ref>Citation error. See inline comment how to fix. {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904046935 by a bug in VisualEditor and later identified by a bot. The original cite can be found at Special:Permalink/903465275 (or in a rev close to it) in either cite #68 or cite #1 - find and verify the cite and replace this template with it (1). [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref>\n\nThe [[urban heat island]] effect does have its toll on Dubai as well, for example during the winter months when temperatures regularly fall to around {{convert|5|C|0|abbr=on}} in the outskirts of the city and its suburbs, the temperatures in Central Dubai rarely fall below {{convert|9|C|0|abbr=on}}. This can be clearly seen when comparing weather data from the city's two airports - [[Dubai International Airport|Dubai International]] and [[Al Maktoum International Airport|Dubai World Central]]. The highest temperature recorded in Dubai is {{convert|48.2|C|0|abbr=on}} reached in July 1996.<ref>Citation error. See inline comment how to fix. {{verify source |date=September 2019 |reason=This ref was deleted Special:Diff/904046935 by a bug in VisualEditor and later identified by a bot. The original cite can be found at Special:Permalink/903465275 (or in a rev close to it) in either cite #70 or cite #2 - find and verify the cite and replace this template with it (1). [[User:GreenC bot/Job 18]]}}</ref> Whereas the lowest recorded temperature in Dubai is {{convert|1|C|0|abbr=on}}.\n\n== Classifications ==\n{{Schemebox\n|city =Dubai\n\n| source_k =<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.weatherbase.com/weather/weather-summary.php3?s=49114&cityname=Dubai,+United+Arab+Emirates|title=Dubai, United Arab Emirates K\u00f6ppen Climate Classification (Weatherbase)|website=Weatherbase|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=MrJiDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA168&lpg=PA168&dq=dubai+koppen+bwh#v=onepage&q=dubai%20koppen%20bwh&f=false|title=Urban Land Systems: An Ecosystems Perspective|last=Millington|first=Andrew|last2=Nagendra|first2=Harini|last3=Kopeck\u00e1|first3=Monika|date=2018-07-02|publisher=MDPI|isbn=9783038429173|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skybrary.aero/index.php/OMDB|title=Dubai International Airport - SKYbrary Aviation Safety|website=www.skybrary.aero|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref>\n| initial_k ={{Redback|''BWh''}}\n| description_k =Hot [[desert climate]]{{efn|Also called tropical and subtropical [[desert climate]]}}\n\n| source_t =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kkh.ltrr.arizona.edu/kkh/climate/trewartha_maps.htm|title=Trewartha maps|website=kkh.ltrr.arizona.edu|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref>\n| initial_t ={{Regional|''BWh''}}\n| description_t =[[Desert climate]]\n\n| source_a =<ref>{{Citation|last=Cmapm|first=Kliimav\u00f6\u00f6tmed svg: Urmasderivative work|title=\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439: \u041a\u043b\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0441\u0430 \u0417\u0435\u043c\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0411. \u041f. \u0410\u043b\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0443.|date=2011-06-16|url=https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Alisov%27s_classification_of_climate_ru.jpg|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref>\n| initial_a ={{n/a}} \n| description_a =[[Tropical climate]]{{efn|Dry [[tropical climate]]}}\n\n| source_s =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://i.pinimg.com/originals/c5/16/b8/c516b8c463fa99df0da778f768c85965.jpg|title=World Strahler Climate Map|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n| initial_s ={{n/a}} \n| description_s =Dry [[tropical climate]]\n\n| source_tw =<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Feddema|first=Johannes J.|date=January 2005|title=A Revised Thornthwaite-Type Global Climate Classification|journal=Physical Geography|language=en|volume=26|issue=6|pages=442\u2013466|doi=10.2747/0272-3646.26.6.442|issn=0272-3646}}</ref>\n| initial_tw =<center>''E A' ''</center>\n| description_tw =Arid and [[megathermal]]\n\n| source_n =<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spektrum.de/lexikon/geographie/klimaklassifikation/4159|title=Klimaklassifikation|website=www.spektrum.de|language=de|access-date=2019-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.klett.de/sixcms/media.php/klett72.a.427.de/upload/klimazonen_neef.jpg|title=Klimazonen nach E. Neef (1989)|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Klett-Perthes|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n| initial_n ={{n/a}}  \n| description_n =Dry climate of [[trade winds]]\n}}\n\n== Climate data ==\n{{Weather box\n| location = Dubai\n| metric first = yes\n| single line = yes\n\n| Jan record high C = 31.6\n| Feb record high C = 37.5\n| Mar record high C = 41.3\n| Apr record high C = 43.5\n| May record high C = 47.0\n| Jun record high C = 46.7\n| Jul record high C = 49.0\n| Aug record high C = 48.7\n| Sep record high C = 45.1\n| Oct record high C = 42.0\n| Nov record high C = 41.0\n| Dec record high C = 35.5\n\n| Jan high C = 22.9\n| Feb high C = 25.4\n| Mar high C = 26.3\n| Apr high C = 33.0\n| May high C = 37.7\n| Jun high C = 39.5\n| Jul high C = 40.9\n| Aug high C = 41.3\n| Sep high C = 38.9\n| Oct high C = 35.4\n| Nov high C = 30.6\n| Dec high 